So this happy barista who just wants to work propaganda just pisses me off so much.

I have endured to much verbal and emotional abuse to just be "wow I just love my shifts!" love to wake up at 4am and get called a bitch, so fun.

We are here to get paid, not to fuck you covid.

If you no shift or low shift someone, they can't file for unemployment. Its a common tactic for forcing a worker to quit, because they can't get extra shifts outside of offering coverage. https://t.co/ztqIxoHI8K

Food service doesn't get holiday pay or vacation, we get pushback if we try to use sick pay even if we get sick pay. Fear of using it in case you really need it later.

Management frequently punishes with bad shifts or no shifts if you piss them off.

We didn't get paid for taking time off unless we filed for unemployment. Which didn't account for tip income, so everyone took a hit without tips.

It's harder to take time off if there is no one to cover shifts, so pressure is put on you by management.

I just keep reflecting on this as a food service worker who worked through the pandemic.

One of the details I enjoyed is the top of the siphon on the counter top holding the coffee paddle, which is the proper way to rest it between stirrings. It's just very cool to me they did such a detailed job with it.

Part of the siphon experience is its brewed to order and it goes through several stages of careful stirring so that the coffee grinds form a muffin top. Once you remove it from heat the water coffee mix at top gets sucked into the lower chamber as the glass temp drops

If you have never had a siphon, it's one of the oldest forms of filtered coffee brewing. It was invented by a woman. It had a resurgence in popularity thanks to Japanese cafés. The end result is a lighter more tea like coffee.
